SPARTA examples and regression tests for the species weighting scheme (SWS)
============================================================================

The SWS assigns each species a weight w_i (column 9 of the species file,
enabled via the SWS or SWSmax keyword of the species command).  The
physical-to-numerical particle ratio for species i is w_i * fnum, so a
trace species with w_i = 0.1 is resolved with 10x more numerical
particles per physical particle.  See doc/species.html.

Inputs
------
in.sws.box      thermal box, N2 (w=1.0) + 10% N (w=0.1), SWS keyword:
                weighted particle creation, weighted NTC collisions,
                split-merge scattering, sumwi grid tally
in.swsmax.box   same box with the SWSmax pair-selection variant
in.sws0.box     same species file with NO keyword: weights must be inert
                and the run identical to a conventional simulation
in.sws.emit     2d channel, weighted inflow via fix emit/face:
                per-species emission targets scaled by 1/w_i
in.sws.chem     hot box with TCE N2 dissociation, single-group mixture:
                probabilistic reactant/product creation/deletion
in.sws.ambi     ambipolar approximation with a weighted trace neutral
                (no reactions; SWS reactions with ambipolar require
                equal ion/electron weights)
in.sws.restart  restart round-trip: the SWS mode flag and weights are
                persisted through write_restart/read_restart

Regression testing
------------------
These inputs are registered as the "sws" ctest suite (see
cmake/common/set/sparta_cmake_defaults.cmake) and are compared
column-by-column against the gold log files log.<date>.mpi_1.<test> by
tools/testing/regression.py, exactly like the other example suites.
The gold logs were generated with a serial build; MPI gold logs are
auto-generated on first run.  To run by hand:

    cd examples/sws
    python3 ../../tools/testing/regression.py mpi_1 \
        /path/to/spa_serial . -logread ../../tools/testing olog

Because all runs use a fixed seed and the comparison tolerance is tight,
any refactor of the SWS code paths that changes trajectories will fail
these tests.  If a change is *intended* to alter results, regenerate the
gold logs and document why.

Physics checks
--------------
verify_sws.py runs seed-independent physical-invariant checks (species
split ~ f_i/w_i, sum(w_i) tallies, steady temperature / no energy leak,
weighted emission ratios, physical mass conservation through reactions):

    cd examples/sws
    python3 verify_sws.py /path/to/spa_serial

Known limitations of the current SWS implementation (enforced by errors)
------------------------------------------------------------------------
- gas-phase chemistry requires a single-group mixture
- surface reactions are not supported
- gas-collision tally computes are not supported
- create_particles species/fractions custom options are not supported
- fix emit/surf custom fractions are not supported
- the KOKKOS package does not implement SWS
